<subSubSection id="C1826517073CFF93FD35F77A68DF4C53" pageId="16" pageNumber="249" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8927369C073CFF93FD35F77A6F244ECA" blockId="16.[710,1305,2179,2602]" pageId="16" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis id="BBECEA8E073CFF93FD35F77A686E4EA2" bold="true" box="[710,865,2179,2208]" pageId="16" pageNumber="249">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4E984D1F073CFF93FC9DF77A6E1F4EA2" authority="J. A. Allen, 1893" authorityName="J. A. Allen" authorityYear="1893" box="[878,1296,2179,2208]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Geomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="16" pageNumber="249" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cherriei">Geomys cherriei J. A. Allen, 1893</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="39F03CC1073CFF93FD34F7566F244ECA" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3799834302" box="[711,1067,2223,2248]" pageId="16" pageNumber="249">“Santa Clara, Costa Rica.”</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8927369C073CFF93FD34F73768DF4C53" blockId="16.[710,1305,2179,2602]" lastBlockId="16.[99,1303,2608,3468]" pageId="16" pageNumber="249">
Placed into subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4E984D1F073CFF93FBD3F7376FC84EED" authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1895" box="[1056,1223,2254,2287]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Macrogeomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="16" pageNumber="249" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Macrogeomys</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4E984D1F073CFF93FB10F737684F4F14" authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1895" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Heterogeomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="16" pageNumber="249" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Heterogeomys</taxonomicName>
considered a subgenus of Or thogeomys by J. L. Patton in 2005 but was resurrected to genus status by T. A. Spradling and colleagues in 2016. Molecular studies suggest that 
<taxonomicName id="4E984D1F073CFF93FC1DF66A6F774FB6" authorityName="J.A.Allen" authorityYear="1893" box="[1006,1144,2451,2484]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Heterogeomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="16" pageNumber="249" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cherriei">H. cherriei</taxonomicName>
is sister to 
<taxonomicName id="4E984D1F073CFF93FD34F642687E4FDE" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[711,881,2491,2524]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Heterogeomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="16" pageNumber="249" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="heterodus">H. heterodus</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4E984D1F073CFF93FC7FF6426FC14FDE" baseAuthorityName="J. A. Allen" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[908,1230,2491,2524]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Orthogeomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="16" pageNumber="249" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="matagalpae">Orthogeomys matagalpae</taxonomicName>
, was formerly recognized as a separate species but was synonymized under 
<taxonomicName id="4E984D1F073CFF93FB97F5F06FE34C28" authorityName="J.A.Allen" authorityYear="1893" box="[1124,1260,2569,2602]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Heterogeomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="16" pageNumber="249" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cherriei">H. cherriei</taxonomicName>
by Spradling and colleagues in 2016. Four subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C1826517073CFF93FF90F5A16F0D4D14" pageId="16" pageNumber="249" type="synonymic_list">
<caption id="DDE76614073CFF93FF90F5A16F0D4D14" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6603875" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6603875" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6603875/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="249" targetBox="[95,686,2183,2598]" targetPageId="16">
